title: Kittens saved from Sydney unit fire - ABC News (Australian Broadcasting Corporation)
text:
Kittens saved from Sydney unit fire Posted February 15, 2017 09:26:09 
Firefighters have rescued a cat and her five kittens from a fire in a unit at Kingswood, in Sydney's west, overnight. 
Emergency services were called to the unit block on Santley Crescent just before 10:00pm on Tuesday. 
They found a fire in a second floor unit. 
No one was injured in the blaze. 
But Fire and Rescue New South Wales Inspector Bob Mey said crews found a number of cats and kittens inside the unit. 
"They rescued [the animals] and brought outside and supplied water to the cats," he said. 
A crime scene was established and police were investigating the cause of the fire.
